# Delivery — {{ project_name }}

Phase 2 of the lifecycle: **Discovery → Delivery → Deployment**. This is the
record of what got *built* between an approved design (G1) and a shippable
build (G2): milestone outcomes, the eval evidence that clears the gate, which
deferred capabilities landed, and — the point of this file — **what delivery
hands to deployment**.

Phase and gate state live in `LIFECYCLE.md` (machine-readable, written by
`/gate-check`). This file is the **human** delivery record and handoff. DESIGN.md
said *what to build and why*; this says *what was built and how we know it works*;
DEPLOYMENT.md picks up from the handoff below to ship it. Keep it current as
milestones close — filled at G2, not reconstructed from memory afterward.

> **Gate G2 is the delivery → deployment handoff.** `/gate-check` records the
> verdict in `LIFECYCLE.md`; `/deploy-check` pre-flights the same criteria on
> launch day. This file supplies the *evidence* those checks read against.

---

## G2 readiness — what "delivered" means

Delivery is not done when the code is written — it's done when the build clears
G2 (per the lifecycle schema in `LIFECYCLE.md`). Each row below is the evidence
`/gate-check` audits:

| G2 check | Evidence (fill in / link the artifact) |
|---|---|
| `eval_gate_green` | `make eval-gate` passes against `{{ eval_root }}/targets.yaml`, incl. the margin-over-naive-baseline row. Last run: <!-- date + result --> |
| `security_review_clean` | `/security-review` run for the shipping commit, no unresolved findings. Artifact: <!-- link --> |
| `sanyi_audit_clean` | `/sanyi audit` passes — no cross-layer contract violations in what's shipping. |
| `deployment_target_resolved` | DESIGN.md's deployment decision is `Resolved` (`{{ deployment_target }}`), not Open/Deferred. |
| `runbook_monitoring_documented` | `DEPLOYMENT.md` Rollout/Rollback/Monitoring sections filled + DESIGN.md operator-model row set. |

